## 5. Middleware Layer Specification

### 5.1 `framework/mcp` — Role Clarification (No Structural Changes)

`framework/mcp` is a **protocol adapter middleware**. It stays exactly where it is. Its role:

- `framework/mcp/protocol`: MCP wire types (revisions 2025-06-18, 2025-11-25)
- `framework/mcp/client`: MCP client as a `Provider` implementation (`ProviderKindMCPClient`)
- `framework/mcp/server`: Exposes Relurpify capabilities as an MCP server for external consumers
- `framework/mcp/transport/stdio`: Stdio transport for child-process MCP servers
- `framework/mcp/mapping`: Import/export between MCP types and `core.CapabilityDescriptor`

**MCP is local-first capable:** an MCP server running as a subprocess (`ProviderKindMCPClient`, `ProviderOriginLocal`) is the same trust class as a builtin tool. Remote MCP servers (`ProviderOriginRemote`) are denied by default under the `deny-remote-by-default` policy rule.

### 5.2 `framework/channel` — New Package (Nexus Ingress Middleware)

The channel adapter interface and lifecycle manager. No concrete adapters here.

```go
package channel

// Adapter normalizes inbound messages from an upstream service.
// All adapter state must be recoverable from the EventLog — the adapter
// itself is stateless.
type Adapter interface {
    // Name returns the channel identifier: "telegram", "discord", "webchat"
    Name() string

    // Start connects to the upstream service and begins receiving messages.
    // Emits EventChannelConnected on success. Retries with backoff on failure.
    Start(ctx context.Context, config json.RawMessage, sink EventSink) error

    // Send delivers an outbound message to the upstream channel.
    Send(ctx context.Context, msg OutboundMessage) error

    // Status returns the adapter's current connection state.
    Status() AdapterStatus

    // Stop disconnects. Emits EventChannelDisconnected.
    Stop(ctx context.Context) error
}

// EventSink receives normalized events from an adapter.
type EventSink interface {
    Emit(ctx context.Context, event core.FrameworkEvent) error
}

// InboundMessage is the canonical normalized message from any channel.
type InboundMessage struct {
    Channel      string          `json:"channel"`
    Account      string          `json:"account,omitempty"`
    Sender       Identity        `json:"sender"`
    Conversation Conversation    `json:"conversation"`
    Content      MessageContent  `json:"content"`
    RawMeta      json.RawMessage `json:"raw_meta,omitempty"`
}

type Identity struct {
    ChannelID   string `json:"channel_id"`
    DisplayName string `json:"display_name,omitempty"`
    ResolvedID  string `json:"resolved_id,omitempty"`
}

type Conversation struct {
    Kind      string `json:"kind"`      // "dm", "group"
    ID        string `json:"id"`
    ThreadID  string `json:"thread_id,omitempty"`
    Mentioned bool   `json:"mentioned"`
}

type MessageContent struct {
    Text      string          `json:"text,omitempty"`
    Media     []MediaRef      `json:"media,omitempty"`
    ReplyTo   string          `json:"reply_to,omitempty"`
    Reaction  string          `json:"reaction,omitempty"`
    Structured json.RawMessage `json:"structured,omitempty"`
}

type MediaRef struct {
    Hash          string `json:"hash"`           // content-addressed object store key
    ContentType   string `json:"content_type"`
    Filename      string `json:"filename,omitempty"`
    SizeBytes     int64  `json:"size_bytes"`
    Transcription string `json:"transcription,omitempty"`
}

type AdapterStatus struct {
    Connected bool
    LastError string
    Reconnects int
}

// OutboundMessage is sent back to a channel by an agent or rule.
type OutboundMessage struct {
    Channel        string         `json:"channel"`
    Account        string         `json:"account,omitempty"`
    ConversationID string         `json:"conversation_id"`
    ThreadID       string         `json:"thread_id,omitempty"`
    Content        MessageContent `json:"content"`
}

// Manager supervises all registered adapters.
// Restarts adapters with exponential backoff on failure.
type Manager struct {
    adapters map[string]Adapter
    sink     EventSink
    log      event.Log
}

func (m *Manager) Register(adapter Adapter) error
func (m *Manager) Start(ctx context.Context, configs map[string]json.RawMessage) error
func (m *Manager) Stop(ctx context.Context) error
func (m *Manager) Send(ctx context.Context, msg OutboundMessage) error
func (m *Manager) Status() map[string]AdapterStatus
```

